The leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra, IPOB, Nnamdi Kanu has raised alarm over fresh attack on its members. Kanu in a post on Sunday night said some security operatives invaded the venue of IPOB gathering and opened fire on them. The incident happened in Ebonyi state during a meeting by the IPOB members The IPOB leader added that some members were seriously injured and in critical condition following the incident. Kanu said this on his official Twitter page. He wrote: “A combined team of security operatives invaded the venue of IPOB gathering in Ebonyi and opened fire on innocent citizens. “Early reports indicate many are seriously injured, with some in critical condition.” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.